The '''Celtic Blue Rock Community Arts Festival''' (known as Blue Rock to locals) is a charity-based [[festival]] showcasing local bands, craftsmen and stalls in [[Llanfyrnach]], [[Wales]]. From small beginnings in 2004, it has grown to be an annual event attracting 10,000 people.<ref name="bbc cancelled">{{cite news|title=Pembrokeshire Celtic Blue Rock festival 2010 cancelled |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/10472549 |work=BBC News |date=1 July 2010 }}</ref>
The festival made the news in 2010 when it was cancelled after it lost its licence due to safety concerns.<ref name="bbc cancelled" /><ref name="w-online 2010">{{cite news|author=Rachel Misstear |title=Celtic Blue Rock festival loses licence over safety fears |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/celtic-blue-rock-festival-loses-1919207 |work=Wales Online |date=20 May 2010 }}</ref>
Performers included former [[Hawkwind]] band member [[Nik Turner]], Thunder Chair, Johnny Action Finger, Session Head, Quantum Beats and The Measurements Group, as well as a number of local bands performing Dance, [[Trance music|Trance]] and [[Drum and Bass]].
